## Automated Communications That Feel Timely, Not Automated

### Confirmation Messages

When someone signs up, they receive immediate confirmation—if you've enabled it. The confirmation email includes all event details, formatted cleanly for reference. It arrives in their preferred language, drawn from their profile or your workspace defaults.

Confirmations respect the "do not contact" flag. If someone has opted out of communications, the system honors that preference automatically.

### Intelligent Reminders

Set reminders to go out one day, three days, a week before your event—whatever timing makes sense for your community. The system tracks what's been sent to prevent duplicates, even if you adjust reminder timing after some messages have already gone out.

Reminders include the same full event context as confirmations: location, time, how to join. For virtual events, the meeting link is prominent. For in-person events, the full address renders clearly. Calendar integration links appear again, for people who didn't add it the first time.

The reminder system is timezone-aware, calculating "24 hours before" based on the event's location, not your server's clock. International communities get accurate timing.

### Cancellation Notifications

When plans change, notify all confirmed attendees with a single action. The system tracks who's been notified to prevent repeated cancellation messages if you need to make multiple updates to the event record.

Cancellations use the same email template as reminders, maintaining visual consistency while clearly communicating the change. Activity logs track every notification sent, giving you an audit trail of who was informed and when.

