## Attendee Management That Informs Strategy

### Real-Time Attendance Tracking

View your signup list as it grows. Filter by status: who's confirmed, who's cancelled, who actually attended. Search by name or email. Each attendee links back to their full profile in your community database, so you see signup information alongside their broader engagement history.

After events, update statuses to reflect reality. Mark who attended, who didn't show. This data flows back into your CRM, enriching your understanding of participation patterns over time.

### Export on Your Terms

Download attendee lists as CSV with configurable columns. Include standard fields—name, email, phone—or add event-specific custom fields. The export respects your selections from the detailed attendee view, so you can create different exports for different purposes: a simple headcount, a detailed follow-up list, or a mailing list for post-event surveys.

Multi-select custom fields export as comma-separated values. Dates format consistently. Boolean fields convert to clear "Yes" / "No" labels. The export is designed for immediate use in spreadsheets or import into other tools—no post-processing required.

### Visual Attendee Lists

Toggle between quick view (names and status) and detailed view (all fields). Print mode creates clean, paper-friendly lists for physical events. Mobile drawers make attendee management work on phones, not just desktop computers.

