## Integration With Your Community Database

### Seamless CRM Connection

Every signup updates your community database intelligently. If someone's email matches an existing profile, their record is updated with new information from the signup form—no duplicate profiles created. If they're new to your community, a complete profile is created automatically.

The system makes smart decisions about what to update. It won't overwrite existing data with blank fields, but it will add missing information. Someone signs up with their phone number for the first time? That's added to their profile. They provide their organization? That's captured too.

### Rich Activity Tracking

Every interaction creates an activity record: the signup itself, confirmation emails sent, reminders delivered, cancellations notified. These activities appear in each person's profile timeline, giving you full context when you're looking at an individual's engagement history.

Activity tracking includes the full event context—event title, date, location—so you can understand what someone participated in without cross-referencing multiple systems.

### Contact Preference Honoring

People who sign up via email are marked as email subscribers. People who sign up via WhatsApp are marked as WhatsApp subscribers. These preferences flow through to future communications, ensuring you reach people on their preferred channel.

The "do not contact" flag is respected universally. If someone has opted out, automated event communications won't reach them—even if they're on the attendee list.

