## Event Lifecycle Management

### Draft and Publish Workflow

Create events in draft mode while you finalize details. Preview exactly how the public page will look before you share it. When you're ready, publish with one click—the public URL becomes active immediately.

Published events can be unpublished if you need to make significant changes. The system doesn't penalize iteration.

### Archive for Posterity

After events conclude, archive them to keep your active event list focused. Archived events remain in your database with all signup information intact—they're just hidden from your main event list. Unarchive anytime if you need to reference details or export attendee lists later.

### Status Indicators

Visual indicators show draft, published, archived, and cancelled events at a glance. Filter your event list by status to focus on what matters right now.

