## Customization and Flexibility

### Event-Specific Fields

Not every event needs the same information. A community meal might need dietary restrictions. A skills workshop might need experience level. A physical mobilization might need emergency contact information.

Create custom fields per event, choosing from text, number, date, boolean, single-select, or multi-select formats. Label them clearly. Mark them as required or optional. Custom fields appear in the signup form, in attendee lists, and in CSV exports—fully integrated with your standard field set.

### Communication Preferences

Toggle signup confirmations on or off per event. Set reminder timing to match your community's patterns—a week's notice for weekend events, 24 hours for weeknight gatherings. Choose whether to display timezone information on public pages, helpful for distributed communities but potentially cluttering for local-only events.

Every event can specify its preferred communication channel, helping you route notifications appropriately across email and WhatsApp.

### Capacity Control

Set maximum signup numbers for space-limited events, or leave it unlimited for virtual gatherings. The counter updates automatically, and the public page displays availability clearly. When capacity is reached, signups can be closed automatically (if configured).

